Nonetheless, 1D “mechanical” models extend beyond the simple arguments of energy or angular momentum conservation used in the formalisms discussed in Sect. 2.1. They attempt a physical description of the dynamical interaction between companion and envelope, albeit in a parametric way: The inspiral of the companion into the envelope is followed according to a drag force acting on it. This model raises questions: (i) What exactly is the nature of the interaction between the companion and the envelope gas and how can the drag force Fdrag\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
