Another explanation of why the orbital separation stabilizes, is that the gravitational force between the cores increases as the cores approach each other. Therefore, one needs a larger drag force to noticeably perturb the orbital separation. Thus when the cores approach each other, maintaining the same rate of inspiral requires a larger and larger force, just when in fact orbit evacuation and a reduction of the velocity contrast is reducing the drag.Fig. 5
