There is yet another, more restrictive reason why CE simulations with resolved cores are unrealistic. It arises from the timescale problem mentioned in Sect. 3.5. The dynamical timescale defined in Eq. (28) is the relevant quantity for estimating the computational cost of the simulation. Generally, hydrodynamic simulations aim to follow the evolution of the modeled system over a duration close to τdyn\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
