				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$1 \, M_\odot $$\end{document} of material is ejected in the evolution, preferentially in the direction of the orbital plane. Based on the multidimensional structure of the outflow, they argued that modeling CE events based on energy conservation arguments alone is insufficient. Applying the same numerical method, Taam and Bodenheimer (1989) explored CEE in a system with a 5M⊙\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
