				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$1.05 \, M_\odot $$\end{document} RG primary star modeled by Ricker and Taam (2008)—in particular in the view of the small time steps required by the CFL condition (see Sect. 5.1). They therefore represented the core of the primary as well as the 0.6M⊙\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
