Another set of grid-based CE simulations was carried out with the AMR code AstroBEAR (Carroll-Nellenback et al. 2013). A few studies have been published so far, concentrating on the analysis of two primary stellar structures and a range of companions. The two structures are an RGB and an AGB star deriving from a 2M⊙\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
