In their paper comparing CE simulations carried out with a grid-based Eulerian code (see Sect. 6.3.2) and SPH, Passy et al. (2012) employed the snsph code of Fryer et al. (2006). It adopts a distributed-memory parallelization (Fryer et al. 2006) and therefore allowed to conduct simulations with enhanced resolution. snsph uses a special tree-based method (a parallel hashed oct-tree, Warren and Salmon 1993) to calculate gravitational accelerations. As in their grid-based counterpart simulations, Passy et al. (2012) followed the interaction of a non-rotating 0.88M⊙\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
