V1309 Sco is a particular system and perhaps not a clear CE case (see Sect. 1.2). A more traditional CE interaction was later simulated by the same group (Nandez et al. 2015) with the goal of modeling the double white dwarf system WD 1001+364. For this purpose, the core of the RG primary was selected to be 0.32M⊙\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
