				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\gtrsim $$\end{document} 60%) was observed.

An interesting new feature in modeling methods was introduced by Prust (2020). Moving-mesh hydrodynamics codes allow for moving boundaries inside the simulated domain (Springel 2010a). As a proof-of-concept, Prust (2020) embedded the companion in a CE simulation in a sphere of 4R⊙\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
