These post-CE binaries are used to constrain the post-CE separation of the remnant core system if we assume that today’s separation is the same as that at the end of the CE interaction. In some cases one can compensate for the fact that the binary may have suffered additional orbital reduction due to magnetic breaking or gravitational wave radiation (e.g., Schreiber and Gänsicke 2003). If the mass of the primary is known, one can derive the mass and the radius of the giant at the beginning of the CE phase, with some assumptions and moderate uncertainties (e.g., De Marco et al. 2011; Zorotovic et al. 2010). This reconstruction allows one to estimate the parameters of the pre-CE system, which, together with the observed post-CE systems parameters, gives a value for αCE\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
